<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7214&amp;p=70999#p70999"><![CDATA[
I have an interesting thought to add that I've found helpful for maintaining momentum over time: Always do slightly less than you *want* to do. It's like you have an energy bar that is constantly refilling on its own very slowly... (I can think of a few games with something like that...). Don't use it up too fast!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3735">GradualGames</a> — Fri Dec 03, 2010 11:10 pm</p><hr />
